OL,3,CEnvironmentalists urge islanders to
OL,4,Crecycle Christmas waste
OL,6,FEnvironmentalists are urging Jersey
OL,7,Fresidents to recycle their Christmas
OL,8,Fwaste, as figures reveal people in the
OL,9,FBritish Isles get through more than
OL,10,F200,000 miles of wrapping paper every
OL,11,Fyear.
OL,13,FAccording to the Department for
OL,14,FEnvironment Food and Rural Affairs
OL,15,F(Defra), people in the British Isles
OL,16,Fthrow away approximately #42 million
OL,17,Fof unwanted presents each Christmas.
OL,19,FMany across the Bailiwicks say they
OL,20,Fare trying to make a difference by
OL,21,Frecycling their Christmas waste.
